Cell["\<\
Exercise 1 : Conceptual questions  on data science and data structures \
[Chapters 1 and 2, TB by Shah]\
\>", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811597523431114*^9, 3.811597554184411*^9}, {
  3.811598863166101*^9, 3.811598863630541*^9}, {3.8115989724110622`*^9, 
  3.81159902004309*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cd8303ff-9ad4-4272-8f87-\
6aee558f2e19"],

Cell["\<\
What is data science? How does it relate to and differ from statistics?\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811597558054982*^9, 3.8115976057370243`*^9}, {
  3.8115988669025307`*^9, 
  3.811598885346279*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a04b0c87-b27a-4c7c-9818-\
9acb7afeb878"],

Cell["\<\
Identify three areas or domains in which data science is being used and \
describe how.\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811597558054982*^9, 3.8115976057370243`*^9}, {
  3.8115988669025307`*^9, 
  3.811598906759768*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4a67ec1d-fb1f-4167-bc97-\
c16f39e03a12"],

Cell["\<\
I have the option today of making a SIM card contract with Lebara. 3GB/month \
per \[Sterling]5, 15GB/month per \[Sterling]10, 30GB/month per \[Sterling]15, \
or unlimited data per \[Sterling]25. I go by bus to work on a 45min \
round-trip a day and during this time I watch movies by Netflix with a stream \
of SD videos with 1.5GB/hour. Assuming that I work 20 days a month, which \
contract should I make?  \
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811597558054982*^9, 3.8115976057370243`*^9}, {
   3.8115988669025307`*^9, 3.811598947701604*^9}, 3.8739673203997087`*^9, 
   3.883633320554978*^9},ExpressionUUID->"542dfc13-03e0-48de-96da-\
2845923fee29"],

Cell["\<\
List at least two differences between structured and unstructured data.\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811597558054982*^9, 
  3.8115976057370243`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3b35e172-57e5-4617-b067-\
4e03f1fb7d64"],

Cell["Give three examples of structured data formats.", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811597558054982*^9, 
  3.8115976393975573`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cd082854-6f17-42fa-85a6-\
114016624ff0"],

Cell["Give three examples of unstructured data formats.", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811597558054982*^9, 
  3.811597641437386*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8f93b7a6-069e-434c-b913-\
49a5e601d9b3"],

Cell["\<\
How will you convert a CSV file to a TSV file? List at least two different \
strategies. \
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811597558054982*^9, 
  3.811597683017454*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"64a7c023-0ed6-432f-a600-\
d2f51c489b5a"],

Cell["\<\
You are looking at employee records. Some have no middle name, some have a \
middle initial, and others have a complete middle name. How do you explain \
such inconsistency in the data? Provide at least two explanations.   

\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811597558054982*^9, 
  3.811597756907136*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b9730cdb-408c-4fba-b018-\
a998dd0083f6"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["", "SlideShowNavigationBar",
 CellTags->
  "SlideShowHeader",ExpressionUUID->"7ba8ced5-5ee4-435f-96d3-6ac8b8ece8da"],

Cell["\<\
Exercise 2 : Try it yourself 2.1 : Data Pre - processing [TB by Shah]\
\>", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811597804139524*^9, 3.811597805420599*^9}, {
  3.8115978863709583`*^9, 
  3.811597908353054*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8bb4aee8-9fcf-41c2-ab77-\
25954fb88c0e"],

Cell["\<\
This exercises trains you to understand how to collect data and organize it \
in a relational type dataset to solve your problem :

This is extracted from your TB page 59, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Try it \
Yourself 2.1: Data Pre-processing\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811598090828949*^9, 3.81159812479241*^9}, {
  3.811835472903613*^9, 3.81183549327288*^9}, {3.811835529839776*^9, 
  3.811835566099328*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"99e85d6e-77f9-4dc3-9ffa-\
42466def6009"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["Imagine you want to open a new bakery, and you are \
trying to figure out which item in the menu will help you to keep maximum \
profit margin. You have the following few options:",
 FontSize->24,
 FontWeight->"Regular"]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811598090828949*^9, 3.81159812479241*^9}, {
  3.811835472903613*^9, 3.81183549327288*^9}, {3.811835529839776*^9, 
  3.8118356110525417`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b7de6f78-51b0-4e66-b377-\
d4de7134ddff"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["For ",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"],
 StyleBox["cookies",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox[", you would need flour, chocolate, butter, and other ingredients, \
which comes at $3.75 per pound (lb). The initial setup cost is $",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"],
 StyleBox["1580",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular",
  FontColor->RGBColor[0, 0, 1]],
 StyleBox[", while the labour charge is another $30 per hour. In one hour you \
can serve two batches of cookies, while making 250 cookies per batch. Each \
batch requires 15lb of ingredients, and each cookie can be priced at $2.",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"]
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811598090828949*^9, 3.81159812479241*^9}, {
   3.811835472903613*^9, 3.81183549327288*^9}, {3.811835529839776*^9, 
   3.8118356223843727`*^9}, {3.8119267514047327`*^9, 3.8119267711260366`*^9}, 
   3.812365157617282*^9, 
   3.977385892296913*^9},ExpressionUUID->"829ddfb9-d5de-4385-88d7-\
b97ac7c2e538"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["For your second option, you can make ",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"],
 StyleBox["cake",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox[" with the same ingredients. However, the ratio of the ingredients \
being different, it will cost you $4 per lb. The initial setup cost is $",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"],
 StyleBox["2000",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular",
  FontColor->RGBColor[0, 0, 1]],
 StyleBox[", while the labour charge remains the same. However, baking two \
batches of cake will require 3 hours in total, with five cakes in each batch. \
Each cake when baked with 2 lb of ingredient can be sold at $34.",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"]
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811598090828949*^9, 3.81159812479241*^9}, {
   3.811835472903613*^9, 3.81183549327288*^9}, {3.811835529839776*^9, 
   3.811835631204544*^9}, {3.811926781238442*^9, 3.811926781449523*^9}, 
   3.977385899481516*^9},ExpressionUUID->"59b9c5c4-26ab-4d0c-93d2-\
f08c149e1fd4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["In the third option, you can make ",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"],
 StyleBox["bagels",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox[" in your shop, which will require flour, butter and other \
ingredients, which will cost you $2.50 per lb. The initial setup cost is low, \
at $",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"],
 StyleBox["680",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular",
  FontColor->RGBColor[0, 0, 1]],
 StyleBox[", as is the labour cost. $25 per hour. In one batch, using 20 lb \
of ingredients, you can make 300 bagels in 45 minutes. Each bagel can be sold \
at $1.75.",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"]
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811598090828949*^9, 3.81159812479241*^9}, {
   3.811835472903613*^9, 3.81183549327288*^9}, {3.811835529839776*^9, 
   3.8118356397592382`*^9}, {3.811926822750106*^9, 3.8119268229743023`*^9}, 
   3.977385897105946*^9},ExpressionUUID->"09e9ddc2-9613-4af2-a9e7-\
a215df8fd44b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["For the fourth and final option, you can bake ",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"],
 StyleBox["loaves of bread",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox[", where you will need only flour and butter for the ingredients, \
which will cost you $3 per lb. The initial setup cost is marginal between $",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"],
 StyleBox["270",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular",
  FontColor->RGBColor[0, 0, 1]],
 StyleBox[" and $",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"],
 StyleBox["350",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular",
  FontColor->RGBColor[0, 0, 1]],
 StyleBox["; however, the labour charge is high, $40 per hour. However, you \
can bake as many as 1000 loaves in 2 hours; each can be priced at $3. Use \
this information to create a dataset that can be used to decide the menu for \
your bakery.",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"],
 "\n"
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811598090828949*^9, 3.81159812479241*^9}, {
   3.811835472903613*^9, 3.81183549327288*^9}, {3.811835529839776*^9, 
   3.811835648207366*^9}, 
   3.977385900736465*^9},ExpressionUUID->"0a59a7dd-6677-419c-8cdc-\
40f470d396b6"]
}, Open  ]]
},
